30,000 Leicester fans to wear Vardy masks to protest his ban.
Leicester Citys owners have given out around 30,000 Jamie Vardy masks to supporters before their home game against Everton on Monday in protest against the strikers three-game suspension.Vardy was banned by the Football Association after being sent off for a two-footed challenge on Mame Biram Diouf during Leicesters recent 2-2 draw at Stoke City.The Premier League champions had an appeal against the punishment rejected, which the Thai chairman, Vichai Srivaddhanaprabha, described as unfair.Leicester go into the game at the King Power Stadium 15th in the Premier League table, three points above the relegation zone.